
This directory contains configuration files for some key components of the core.
The idea is that these files can be used to generate as many different things as
possible, though not everything is possible at this time.

Running make will first of all patch source code. Then it will try to regenerate
the PDF documentation, which may fail if you don't have all the required LaTeX
packages installed.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cregs
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Describes the context control registers and the global control registers of the
core.

  Completely specifies:
   - C header/assembly include files (rvex.h)
   - Documentation
  
  TODO:
   - Default memory map for rvd
   - VHDL core
   - Simulator
  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
opcodes
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Describes the rvex instruction set.

  Completely specifies:
   - VHDL core
   - Documentation
  
  TODO:
   - Simulator
  
  Does NOT specify:
   - Binutils
   - Compilers

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
traps
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Describes the hardware traps.

  Completely specifies:
   - C header/assembly include files (rvex.h)
   - Documentation
  
  TODO:
   - Default memory map for rvd
  
  Only specifies ID constants for each trap (not functionality):
   - Nothing yet :(
  
  TODO:
   - VHDL core
   - Simulator

